x4freetext: The 10B and 11B targets were both prepared by
evaporation of the enriched  metals (92% and 98.6%
respectively) using the electron bombardment technique
described by Muggleton and Howe).Both targets were
about 50 mu-g/cm**2 in thickness and in the case of 11B
a thin carbon backing was used.This later permitted
measurements to be made of the higher excited states of
been measured in a number of cases and these were
determined either by directly weighing the targets or
by making separate measurements of the elastically
scattered tritons.The former method is considered
accurate to only +-30% and the latter to +-10%.
